@startuml

title **Basic Generalization Hierarchy**\nModules organized through the //is-a// relation

!include ../../../../../../tooling/styles/plantuml/structural/class-diagram-style.iuml

abstract class "AbstractModule" as AM #D5E8D4 {
  + commonOperation()
  {abstract} + variationPoint()
  # sharedState
}

class "ConcreteModuleA" as CMA {
  + variationPoint()
  + specializedOpA()
}

class "ConcreteModuleB" as CMB {
  + variationPoint()
  + specializedOpB()
}

class "FurtherSpecialized" as FS #F0F0F0 {
  + additionalOp()
}

AM <|-- CMA : is-a
AM <|-- CMB : is-a
CMA <|-- FS : is-a

note right of AM
  **Parent (General)**
  Defines common interface
  and shared behavior.
end note

note bottom of CMA
  **Child (Specialized)**
  Inherits parent interface,
  provides specific implementation.
end note

legend bottom
  Hollow triangle arrowhead points toward the **parent** (more general module).
  Children inherit and may override parent behavior.
end legend

@enduml

